body:
Hello there, fellow Boards users.

In this PSA I will show you how to properly use   &macr;\\\_(ツ)_/&macr; as I notice quite frequently people attempting to use: 

 &macr;\\\_(ツ)_/&macr; 

But ending up with:

 &macr;\_(ツ)_/&macr; 



To properly use  &macr;\\\_(ツ)_/&macr; , simply put a double backslash right before or after the backslash already present.

Doing so will get you this when you are typing up a post on Boards:
 &macr;\\\\\\\_(ツ)_/&macr; 

Which will give you the correct form of  &macr;\\\_(ツ)_/&macr; 

This has been your friendly neighborhood PSA, in an attempt to stop the abhorrent misuse of  &macr;\\\_(ツ)_/&macr;
